The Laredo gateway is the primary gateway for the KCSM, and we'd have to do two things. We have to make sure that operationally, we're treated fairly and equitably at the gateway. And then we have to make sure commercially that we're treated fairly and equitably to all the points that we currently have an opportunity to serve with our franchise in the United States in conjunction with KCSM. Our franchise is damn good. It's the best in the industry, and that's why we represent about 2/3 of all rail cross-border traffic to and from Mexico. It could be a cry in shame, and it would be against what the STB has committed they would do in evaluating the merger if that excellence is replaced by something that's inferior, and it's because we're disadvantaged. So we'll be crystal clear about that in front of the STB and in the process.

